{"lemma":"أَشَمّ","slug":"أَشَمّ","root":"ش.م.م","root_slug":"ش-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22944"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"smelling fine, having a good nose"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"high, elevated","examples":[{"text":"ثُمَّ رحلنا منها، فوصلنا إلى مدينة ماردين، وهي عظيمة في سطح جبل. من أحسن مدن الإسلام وأبدعها وأتقنها وأحسنها أسواقًا. وبها تصنع الثياب المنسوبة إليها من الصُّوف المعروف بالمرعز. ولها قلعة شمَّاء من مشاهير القلاع في قُنَّة جبلها.","english":"Iraq and Persia"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"haughty, supercilious"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make smell","tags":["ditransitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ش م م (š m m).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/ʔa.ʃamm/","/ʔa.ʃam.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22944","headword_ar":"اَشَمُّ","root":"$m","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a man, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having that quality of the nose which is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amamN","text_ar":"شَمَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$am~u AlA^anofi","text_ar":"اَشَمُّ الاَنْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus applied: (S:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$am~aA='u","text_ar":"شَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) and pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$um~N","text_ar":"شُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  And [hence, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Self-magnifying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proud,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haughty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] a chief"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"characterized by disdainfulness, scornfulness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disdainful and proud incompliance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and high-minded."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also A mountain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"High,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as applied to a place of ascent in a mountain: see an ex. of the pl. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSad~afa","text_ar":"تَصَدَّفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  And A shoulder"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high in the head of its bone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b5-  [Freytag mentions two other meanings: ―         -b6-  “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ventus ex alto veniens, qui penetrantioris est odoratus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b7-  [and] fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$am~aA'","text_ar":"شَمَّاء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Jugum extensum in monte:"},{"kind":"text","text":"” from the Deewán of the Hudhalees.]"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","TA","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}